The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of the Steiner Multicut problem, which is a graph cut problem. This makes it likely to belong to categories related to graph theory and algorithms. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are all relevant categories. Additionally, the paper uses structural lemmas and proofs by contradiction, which are techniques commonly used in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT).
